<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871020-0126 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:M.A. Hanna Co.</HL><DD> 10/20/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> HNMTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><TEXT>   M.A. Hanna Co., Cleveland, said it reached a definitive agreement to buy PMS Consolidated, which makes colorants for the plastics industry, for about $44 million in stock and cash.    Hanna, which has interests in formulated polymers, energy and minerals and metals businesses, said it would pay for the transaction in part by issuing $2.125 convertible exchangeable preferred stock, which will have a market value as of the acquisition date of about $18 million. The balance will be paid in cash.    Hanna said it expected the transaction to be completed near the end of the month. PMS, Somerset, N.J., had revenue of more than $70 million in its last fiscal year, which ended in May. </TEXT></DOC>